8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 266, L.D. 412, “An Act to Prohibit the
10 Sale or Provision of Self-administered Sexual Assault Forensic Evidence Collection Kits”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Prohibit the Sale of Self-administered Sexual Assault Forensic Evidence
13 Collection Kits'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 25 MRSA §2915-A is enacted to read:
17 §2915-A. Sale of self-administered sexual assault forensic evidence collection kit
18 prohibited
19 1. Definitions. As used in this section, the following terms have the following
20 meanings.
21 A. "Person" has the same meaning as in Title 5, section 206, subsection 2.
22 B. "Self-administered sexual assault forensic evidence collection kit" means materials
23 advertised or marketed as a means for a person other than a licensed hospital or licensed
24 health care practitioner to collect physical evidence of a sexual assault.
25 C. "Sexual assault" has the same meaning as in section 2915, subsection 3-A.
26 2. Prohibition. A person may not sell or offer for sale a self-administered sexual
27 assault forensic evidence collection kit.
28 3. Admissibility. This section does not affect the admissibility in a court proceeding
29 of evidence collected using a self-administered sexual assault forensic evidence collection
30 kit.
31 4. Violation. There is a rebuttable presumption that a violation of this section is a
32 violation of the Maine Unfair Trade Practices Act.'
