COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 266, L.D. 412
1 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
2 number to read consecutively.
3 SUMMARY
44 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment prohibits the
55 sale or offering for sale of materials advertised or marketed as a means for a person other
66 than a licensed hospital or licensed health care practitioner to collect physical evidence of
77 a sexual assault, referred to in the amendment as a self-administered sexual assault forensic
88 evidence collection kit, and establishes a rebuttable presumption that a violation of this
99 prohibition is a violation of the Maine Unfair Trade Practices Act. The amendment also
1100 clarifies that this prohibition does not affect the admissibility in a court proceeding of
1111 evidence collected using a self-administered sexual assault forensic evidence collection kit.
1122 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
